 The moral element played an important part in the above experiments. The workpeople told the factory inspector: We work with more spirit, we have the reward ever before us of getting away sooner at night, and one active and cheerful spirit pervades the whole mill, from the youngest piecer to the oldest hand, and we can greatly help each other. (l.c., p. 21.) 

