 Even J. B. Say says: Les épargnes des riches se font aux dépens des pauvres. [the savings of the rich are made at the expense of the poor] The Roman proletarian lived almost entirely at the expense of society.... It can almost be said that modern society lives at the expense of the proletarians, on what it keeps out of the remuneration of labour. (Sismondi: études, &c., t. i., p. 24.) 

